*   ^ Wikipedia [article pages](/Wikipedia:NSO) (and various navigational pages: categories, [navboxes](/Wikipedia:Navigation_template), disambiguation pages, etc.) are off-limits for any advocacy. [Talk pages](/Wikipedia:TP), [user pages](/Wikipedia:User_pages), and [essays](/Wikipedia:Essays) are venues where opinions can be expressed, provided they are directly related to the improvement of Wikipedia and are not disruptive.
*   ^ The [English Wikipedia](/English_Wikipedia) incorporates many images and some text considered "fair use" into its [free content](/Free_content) articles. Other language Wikipedias often do not. See also [Wikipedia:Copyrights](/Wikipedia:Copyrights).
*   ^ The restriction on "how-to" content does not apply to the [project namespace](/Wikipedia:Project_namespace), where ["how-to" guides relevant to editing Wikipedia itself](/Category:Wikipedia_how-to), such as [Wikipedia:How to draw a diagram with Dia](/Wikipedia:How_to_draw_a_diagram_with_Dia), are appropriate.
